        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-11-25 15:37:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> (13 comments)\n> \n> Still outstanding for discussion:\n> Do we keep this code here (in API and in PAP) or push it to policy.models?\n> What test do we use to determine whether the connection should be retried? How do we parameterize the test if necessary?\n> \n> Also need to decide how to parameterize delayPeriod\n\nperhaps, in policy/models, we could just add an additional method to the connection factory class, containing this retry logic.  If we do that, then an optional delayPeriod (or retryTime) could be added to the Param class, along with a field containing an array of strings to match",
